### Migrate Payload CMS Plugins to Named Exports

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/migration-guide/overview.mdx

Payload CMS plugins now standardize on named exports with a `Plugin` suffix, moving away from default exports. This change requires updating import statements for all plugins, as shown with `seoPlugin` and `stripePlugin`.

```diff
- import seo from '@payloadcms/plugin-seo'
+ import { seoPlugin } from '@payloadcms/plugin-seo'

- import stripePlugin from '@payloadcms/plugin-stripe'
+ import { stripePlugin } from '@payloadcms/plugin-stripe'

// and so on for every plugin
```

