### Migrate Payload CMS Cloud Storage Plugin S3 Adapter

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/migration-guide/overview.mdx

The `@payloadcms/plugin-cloud-storage` package has moved its individual adapters, like S3, into standalone packages such as `@payloadcms/storage-s3`. This code illustrates migrating from the old plugin-based S3 configuration to the new, more streamlined standalone S3 storage plugin, which simplifies setup and manages peer dependencies more effectively.

```tsx
// ❌ Before (required peer dependencies depending on adapter)

import { cloudStorage } from '@payloadcms/plugin-cloud-storage'
import { s3Adapter } from '@payloadcms/plugin-cloud-storage/s3'

plugins: [
    cloudStorage({
      collections: {
        media: {
          adapter: s3Adapter({
            bucket: process.env.S3_BUCKET,
            config: {
              credentials: {
                accessKeyId: process.env.S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID,
                secretAccessKey: process.env.S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY,
              },
              region: process.env.S3_REGION,
            },
          }),
        },
      },
    }),
  ],

 // ✅ After

 import { s3Storage } from '@payloadcms/storage-s3'

 plugins: [
    s3Storage({
      collections: {
        media: true,
      },
      bucket: process.env.S3_BUCKET,
      config: {
        credentials: {
          accessKeyId: process.env.S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID,
          secretAccessKey: process.env.S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY,
        },
        region: process.env.S3_REGION,
      },
    }),
  ],
```

