### Migrate admin.favicon to admin.icons Array with TypeScript Configuration

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/migration-guide/overview.mdx

The admin.favicon property has been replaced with admin.icons, which now accepts an array of icon objects with path and sizes properties. This change allows for multiple icon configurations and better control over favicon sizes.

```typescript
// payload.config.ts
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'

const config = buildConfig({
  // ...
  admin: {
-   favicon: 'path-to-favicon.svg',
+   icons: [{
+     path: 'path-to-favicon.svg',
+     sizes: '32x32'
+   }]
  }
})
```

