### Replace `react-i18n` `Trans` with Payload `Translation` Component

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/migration-guide/overview.mdx

Payload CMS has removed `react-i18n`, requiring migration from the `Trans` component to the new Payload-provided `Translation` component. The `Translation` component uses an `elements` prop to handle nested components within translated strings.

```diff
'use client'\n- import { Trans } from "react-i18n"\n+ import { Translation } from "@payloadcms/ui"\n\n// Example string to translate:\n// "loggedInChangePassword": "To change your password, go to your <0>account</0> and edit your password there."\n\nexport const MyComponent = () => {\n  return (\n-     <Trans i18nKey="loggedInChangePassword" t={t}>\n-       <Link to={`${admin}/account`}>account</Link>\n-     </Trans>\n\n+     <Translation\n+       t={t}\n+       i18nKey="authentication:loggedInChangePassword"\n+       elements={{\n+         '0': ({ children }) => <Link href={`${admin}/account`} children={children} />,\n+       }}\n+     />\n  )\n}
```

