### Extend Database Schema with Custom Table using beforeSchemaInit Hook in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/postgres.mdx

Demonstrates using the beforeSchemaInit hook to add custom tables to the database schema before Payload builds it. This hook allows extending the database with tables not managed by Payload, useful for preserving existing database structures during migration.

```typescript
import { postgresAdapter } from '@payloadcms/db-postgres'
import {
  integer,
  pgTable,
  serial,
} from '@payloadcms/db-postgres/drizzle/pg-core'

postgresAdapter({
  beforeSchemaInit: [
    ({ schema, adapter }) => {
      return {
        ...schema,
        tables: {
          ...schema.tables,
          addedTable: pgTable('added_table', {
            id: serial('id').notNull(),
          }),
        },
      }
    },
  ],
})
```

