### Configure Postgres Database Adapter in Payload CMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/ADAPTERS.md

This snippet shows how to configure the PostgreSQL database adapter for Payload CMS using `postgresAdapter`. It sets up a connection pool with a connection string sourced from `DATABASE_URI`, explicitly disables automatic schema pushes (`push: false`), and specifies a directory for database migrations (`./migrations`). This configuration is suitable for relational database setups requiring manual migration control.

```ts
import { postgresAdapter } from '@payloadcms/db-postgres'

export default buildConfig({
  db: postgresAdapter({
    pool: {
      connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URI,
    },
    push: false, // Don't auto-push schema changes
    migrationDir: './migrations',
  }),
})
```
